Real Madrid defender, Dani Carvajal has signed a three-year extension to his contract with the club, the Spanish giants said Thursday.  Spain international right back Carvajal, 29, would have seen his old deal expire at the end of June 2022. A club statement read: “Real Madrid and Dani Carvajal have agreed to extend the player’s contract, which will remain linked to the club for the next four seasons, until June 30, 2025.”